Program: Outlook
Title: 22/11/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00lk84w
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 23 Nov 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, Mary Luz Avendano, who's a Colombian journalist forced into exile after receiving death threats. Also, Ghanaian-British documentary maker Yaba Badoe describes her experiences in a camp in Ghana that offers a refuge to women accused of witchcraft. And former supermodel Cameron Alborzian explains how he can solve the problems of Afghanistan - through meditation. Show less